******
[2]
Date: Tue 24 Nov 2015
Source: Great Falls Tribune [edited]
http://www.greatfallstribune.com/story/news/local/2015/11/24/costco-chicken-salad-pulled-ecoli-worries/76320100/


The Department of Public Health and Human Services, along with the CDC, notified Costco customers on Tue 24 Nov 2015 to not eat chicken salad purchased at the store between 18 Oct 2015 to 23 Nov 2015 because of _E. coli_ concerns.

Since late October 2015, 6 people in Gallatin, Lewis and Clark, and Yellowstone counties have become ill from _E. coli_ bacteria. Two of those people were hospitalized, officials said.

The cases are part of a larger outbreak involving multiple states. The origin of the outbreak is unknown.

Others states with confirmed _E. coli_ cases linked to Costco chicken salad include Colorado, Utah and Washington, officials said.

Investigations have determined Costco chicken salad to be a risk factor. Costco already has voluntarily removed the chicken salad, item No. 37719, from its shelves, and no other products are a concern at this time, DPHHS officials said.

--
Communicated by:
