[Chicken as well as turkey are unusual primary sources of enterohemorrhagic _E. coli_ infections in humans. It is possible that another ingredient in the chicken salad is the vehicle or that the chicken was cross-contaminated with the pathogen during or after cooking by poor kitchen hygiene. ProMED awaits more information regarding the scope and source of this ongoing outbreak.

The 1st post states that 7 states are involved, but only Montana, Utah, Colorado, and Washington have been named. - Mod.LL]
